1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:04,087
<b>[Edward] </b><i><b>Do you think the press conference</b></i>
<i><b>changed Edong's mind?</b></i>

2
00:00:04,170 --> 00:00:05,380
<b>[Alice] </b><i><b>We're not sure.</b></i>

3
00:00:05,463 --> 00:00:07,799
<i><b>Regardless if Edong believes us or not,</b></i>
<i><b>we have to come clean.</b></i>

4
00:00:09,509 --> 00:00:12,345
<i><b>For so long, I've dreamed</b></i>
<i><b>of sending my father to prison.</b></i>

5
00:00:12,429 --> 00:00:14,305
<i><b>Of finally getting justice for Mama.</b></i>

6
00:00:14,389 --> 00:00:17,726
<i><b>Erica, I came here because</b></i>
<i><b>there's something I want to give you.</b></i>

7
00:00:17,809 --> 00:00:20,895
<i><b>These are birthday cards I made for you.</b></i>

8
00:00:20,979 --> 00:00:25,442
<i><b>I kept them all because in my mind…</b></i>
<i><b>my sister might still come back.</b></i>

9
00:00:25,525 --> 00:00:26,943
<i><b>Uncle, I was wondering…</b></i>

10
00:00:27,027 --> 00:00:30,989
<i><b>do you know of a house that has</b></i>
<i><b>a lot of antiques or something like that?</b></i>

11
00:00:31,072 --> 00:00:32,615
<i><b>Is that place familiar to you?</b></i>

12
00:00:32,699 --> 00:00:34,617
<b>[scoffs] </b><i><b>No, no, no. I'll get going now.</b></i>

13
00:00:35,535 --> 00:00:38,663
<i><b>-Auntie! You should've called me.</b></i>
<i><b>-Over there.</b></i>

14
00:00:45,211 --> 00:00:47,422
<b>[Erica] </b><i><b>We've been trying to</b></i>
<i><b>correct the mistake of the past.</b></i>

15
00:00:48,339 --> 00:00:51,301
<i><b>-It's not too late, Edong.</b></i>
<b>-They really screwed up Edong.</b>

16
00:00:51,384 --> 00:00:52,635
<b>We're on Edong's side!</b>

17
00:00:52,719 --> 00:00:54,804
<b>[chanting] Edong! Edong! Edong!</b>

18
00:00:54,888 --> 00:00:56,848
<b>-Look at those morons.</b>
<b>-[laughs]</b>

19
00:00:56,931 --> 00:01:00,060
<b>What are they doing?</b>
<b>They must've gone mad.</b>

20
00:01:00,143 --> 00:01:04,606
<b>-[laughing]</b>
<b>-Edong! Edong! Edong!</b>

21
00:01:05,565 --> 00:01:07,859
<b>-[Edong whistling "Sabay Sabay Tayo"]</b>
<b>-[reporter] </b><i><b>Breaking news.</b></i>

22
00:01:07,942 --> 00:01:11,529
<i><b>After the discovery</b></i>
<i><b>of Esther Castro's body</b></i>

23
00:01:11,613 --> 00:01:14,908
<i><b>and the murder of</b></i>
<i><b>Anton Montenegro here in Amurao,</b></i>

24
00:01:14,991 --> 00:01:19,204
<i><b>-another incident…</b></i>
<b>-[audio becomes distorted]</b>

25
00:01:20,705 --> 00:01:24,209
<b>[whistling continues]</b>

26
00:01:24,918 --> 00:01:26,753
<i><b>-Her throat was slashed.</b></i>
<b>-[man] Love, wait!</b>

27
00:01:26,836 --> 00:01:28,797
<i><b>Authorities point to one suspect…</b></i>

28
00:01:28,880 --> 00:01:31,591
<b>[distorted audio]</b>

29
00:01:31,674 --> 00:01:34,719
<i><b>…escaped inmate Edong Santiago,</b></i>

30
00:01:34,803 --> 00:01:38,181
<i><b>who appears</b></i>
<i><b>determined to spill blood in Amurao.</b></i>

31
00:01:39,015 --> 00:01:41,768
<i><b>So, stay alert… </b></i><b>[distorted audio]</b>

32
00:01:41,851 --> 00:01:44,687
<b>-[screams] Aah!</b>
<b>-What's wrong, love?</b>

33
00:01:45,980 --> 00:01:47,607
<b>[woman whimpers]</b>

34
00:01:50,401 --> 00:01:57,200
<b>[theme music playing]</b>

35
00:03:05,977 --> 00:03:07,145
<b>[Christina] Over there.</b>

36
00:03:07,228 --> 00:03:08,646
<b>Over there.</b>

37
00:03:08,730 --> 00:03:14,193
<b>[unsettling music playing]</b>

38
00:03:15,820 --> 00:03:17,780
<b>-[Alice] You need water?</b>
<b>-Alice?</b>

39
00:03:17,864 --> 00:03:18,823
<b>Over there.</b>

40
00:03:19,324 --> 00:03:21,034
<b>-What's going on?</b>
<b>-Over there.</b>

41
00:03:21,117 --> 00:03:24,412
<b>Aunty Christina keeps pointing at</b>
<b>something and saying “over there,”</b>

42
00:03:24,495 --> 00:03:26,581
<b>but I can't figure out what she wants.</b>

43
00:03:26,664 --> 00:03:28,583
<b>-[Christina] There.</b>
<b>-She does that sometimes.</b>

44
00:03:28,666 --> 00:03:31,419
<b>-Over there.</b>
<b>-I often can't understand her.</b>

45
00:03:31,502 --> 00:03:34,297
<b>There was one time</b>
<b>I thought she had seen Edong.</b>

46
00:03:35,256 --> 00:03:36,799
<b>I ended up screaming in fear.</b>

47
00:03:36,883 --> 00:03:37,967
<b>-[chuckles]</b>
<b>-[Christina] Over there.</b>

48
00:03:39,344 --> 00:03:41,930
<b>Can you help me get</b>
<b>her back to her room for now?</b>

49
00:03:42,013 --> 00:03:43,848
<b>Let's just settle her in the living room.</b>

50
00:03:43,932 --> 00:03:46,476
<b>I'll turn on the TV. She likes that.</b>

51
00:03:46,559 --> 00:03:47,727
<b>Okay.</b>

52
00:03:47,810 --> 00:03:50,480
<b>[music fades]</b>

53
00:03:51,564 --> 00:03:55,318
<b>Well, at least now you can</b>
<b>say you're married to an ex-con.</b>

54
00:03:56,736 --> 00:04:00,990
<b>Sounds cool, right?</b>
<b>Do I look like a bad boy now?</b>

55
00:04:01,074 --> 00:04:04,494
<b>Yeah, right. You just</b>
<b>spent three nights in a jail cell.</b>

56
00:04:04,577 --> 00:04:06,371
<b>You weren't even charged.</b>

57
00:04:07,664 --> 00:04:09,958
<b>But love, let's not joke about that.</b>

58
00:04:10,041 --> 00:04:12,335
<b>I'm serious. Let's stop.</b>

59
00:04:12,418 --> 00:04:15,838
<b>Love, I'd rather just joke about it</b>

60
00:04:15,922 --> 00:04:18,549
<b>than get traumatized thinking</b>
<b>about everything that happened.</b>

61
00:04:20,510 --> 00:04:25,306
<b>After I got locked up and</b>
<b>after your press conference,</b>

62
00:04:25,932 --> 00:04:27,934
<b>you know people would say</b>

63
00:04:28,017 --> 00:04:30,603
<b>all kinds of hurtful things about us.</b>

64
00:04:30,687 --> 00:04:32,981
<b>I'm fine. Don't worry.</b>

65
00:04:33,064 --> 00:04:35,108
<b>-I'm ready.</b>
<b>-Mm?</b>

66
00:04:35,191 --> 00:04:38,736
<b>Just tell them, “I'm living my truth.”</b>

67
00:04:38,820 --> 00:04:41,114
<b>That's English! I'm so smart, aren't I?</b>

68
00:04:41,197 --> 00:04:43,157
<b>-Jeez.</b>
<b>-I picked that up in jail.</b>

69
00:04:43,241 --> 00:04:45,326
<b>My cellmate's girlfriend used to visit him</b>

70
00:04:45,410 --> 00:04:48,913
<b>and make him watch</b>
<b>self-affirmation videos.</b>

71
00:04:48,997 --> 00:04:51,291
<b>-Affirmation!</b>
<b>-Affirmation!</b>

72
00:04:51,374 --> 00:04:53,710
<b>-Wow, so positive.</b>
<b>-[chuckles]</b>

73
00:04:53,793 --> 00:04:55,044
<b>[sighs]</b>

74
00:04:56,713 --> 00:04:59,048
<b>-But, love,</b>
<b>-Hmm?</b>

75
00:04:59,132 --> 00:05:03,219
<b>since we're talking about the truth…</b>

76
00:05:04,429 --> 00:05:07,765
<b>and I don't want to keep</b>
<b>anything from you anymore…</b>

77
00:05:10,310 --> 00:05:12,687
<b>there's something</b>
<b>I need to confess to you.</b>

78
00:05:19,360 --> 00:05:21,696
<b>I almost left you and Chloe back then.</b>

79
00:05:23,865 --> 00:05:25,616
<b>She was only one year old.</b>

80
00:05:25,700 --> 00:05:32,332
<b>[melancholic music playing]</b>

81
00:05:32,415 --> 00:05:33,708
<b>[Beth] </b><i><b>Ryan.</b></i>

82
00:05:34,292 --> 00:05:36,544
<i><b>I tried to do the right thing.</b></i>

83
00:05:37,462 --> 00:05:41,007
<i><b>Even though I never saw</b></i>
<i><b>myself as a wife or a mother.</b></i>

84
00:05:42,800 --> 00:05:44,844
<i><b>Now that I'm here,</b></i>

85
00:05:46,179 --> 00:05:52,060
<i><b>I realized I can't love</b></i>
<i><b>you the way you want me to.</b></i>

86
00:05:54,270 --> 00:05:58,858
<i><b>And I can't love Chloe</b></i>
<i><b>the way a child should be loved.</b></i>

87
00:05:59,400 --> 00:06:02,820
<b>[sobs, sniffles]</b>

88
00:06:03,780 --> 00:06:10,203
<b>[melancholic music continues]</b>

89
00:06:10,286 --> 00:06:12,038
<i><b>I'm so sorry, Ryan.</b></i>

90
00:06:27,804 --> 00:06:34,602
<b>[melancholic music continues]</b>

91
00:06:37,438 --> 00:06:40,233
<b>[sobs]</b>

92
00:06:43,945 --> 00:06:49,367
<b>-[engine revving]</b>
<b>-[music fades]</b>

93
00:06:49,450 --> 00:06:51,536
<i><b>Just my luck!</b></i>

94
00:06:52,161 --> 00:06:57,500
<i><b>People who sleep with</b></i>
<i><b>married men, really ruin my day.</b></i>

95
00:06:57,583 --> 00:07:02,505
<i><b>Seeing people</b></i>
<i><b>who looks like a squid is even worse!</b></i>

96
00:07:02,588 --> 00:07:05,675
<i><b>-What did you say?</b></i>
<i><b>-What? Bring it on!</b></i>

97
00:07:13,182 --> 00:07:15,476
<i><b>I was looking for the tree.</b></i>

98
00:07:15,560 --> 00:07:17,937
<i><b>But the fruit showed up instead.</b></i>

99
00:07:18,020 --> 00:07:21,274
<i><b>I guess I have no choice</b></i>
<i><b>now but to stare at an eyesore.</b></i>

100
00:07:23,234 --> 00:07:26,737
<i><b>You could look in</b></i>
<i><b>the mirror to see a bigger eyesore.</b></i>

101
00:07:26,821 --> 00:07:29,323
<b>[sniffling]</b>

102
00:07:30,867 --> 00:07:33,327
<i><b>Have you seen your father around?</b></i>

103
00:07:36,372 --> 00:07:38,416
<i><b>Hey, I'm asking you nicely.</b></i>

104
00:07:39,125 --> 00:07:41,127
<i><b>Just leave me alone, will you?!</b></i>

105
00:07:41,210 --> 00:07:43,045
<i><b>Stop picking a fight.</b></i>

106
00:07:45,756 --> 00:07:47,216
<b>[sobs]</b>

107
00:07:47,300 --> 00:07:49,010
<i><b>Are you okay?</b></i>

108
00:07:51,012 --> 00:07:53,598
<i><b>I'm sure you'll tell</b></i>
<i><b>everyone in Amurao about this.</b></i>

109
00:07:53,681 --> 00:07:56,058
<i><b>That the girl who was</b></i>
<i><b>supposed to become a famous journalist</b></i>

110
00:07:56,893 --> 00:08:00,188
<i><b>so she can snob you, her sperm donor,</b></i>

111
00:08:00,271 --> 00:08:02,023
<i><b>and everyone here in Amurao,</b></i>

112
00:08:02,106 --> 00:08:05,693
<i><b>ended up at the bus terminal,</b></i>
<i><b>alone, crying,</b></i>

113
00:08:05,776 --> 00:08:07,820
<i><b>leaving her husband and daughter.</b></i>

114
00:08:09,363 --> 00:08:10,948
<i><b>You're leaving them?</b></i>

115
00:08:14,327 --> 00:08:17,705
<i><b>You're probably</b></i>
<i><b>thrilled this happened, huh?</b></i>

116
00:08:17,788 --> 00:08:19,707
<i><b>I became a teen mom,</b></i>

117
00:08:19,790 --> 00:08:22,835
<i><b>not even sure if</b></i>
<i><b>I could go back to college.</b></i>

118
00:08:24,879 --> 00:08:30,134
<i><b>I talked big and all only</b></i>
<i><b>to end up like my mother.</b></i>

119
00:08:31,010 --> 00:08:34,305
<b>[sniffles] </b><i><b>But I don't want</b></i>
<i><b>them to think of me like that.</b></i>

120
00:08:34,847 --> 00:08:39,060
<i><b>Like this is how far I go</b></i>
<i><b>or this is all I could achieve.</b></i>

121
00:08:41,020 --> 00:08:41,938
<b>[sniffles]</b>

122
00:08:43,564 --> 00:08:47,818
<i><b>Among Danilo's</b></i>
<i><b>illegitimate children, you're different.</b></i>

123
00:08:47,902 --> 00:08:49,320
<b>[Beth scoffs]</b>

124
00:08:49,862 --> 00:08:53,074
<i><b>You never made him feel</b></i>
<i><b>that you needed his commitment.</b></i>

125
00:08:53,991 --> 00:08:56,577
<i><b>But we both know that's not true.</b></i>

126
00:08:57,578 --> 00:08:59,872
<i><b>Your conviction is admirable.</b></i>

127
00:08:59,956 --> 00:09:03,668
<i><b>But don't you think</b></i>
<i><b>your husband and your daughter</b></i>

128
00:09:03,751 --> 00:09:06,796
<i><b>deserve the same commitment from you?</b></i>

129
00:09:08,506 --> 00:09:11,717
<i><b>I mean, really? You can abandon them?</b></i>

130
00:09:11,801 --> 00:09:16,597
<i><b>For what? For a kind of life</b></i>
<i><b>that others would approve of?</b></i>

131
00:09:21,185 --> 00:09:23,271
<i><b>When you were talking,</b></i>

132
00:09:23,896 --> 00:09:28,651
<i><b>you kept blabbing about</b></i>
<i><b>others, what they would think,</b></i>

133
00:09:28,734 --> 00:09:32,738
<i><b>their respect,</b></i>
<i><b>and how you are so afraid of them.</b></i>

134
00:09:32,822 --> 00:09:34,574
<i><b>What about what you want?</b></i>

135
00:09:34,657 --> 00:09:37,952
<i><b>What do you really want for yourself?</b></i>

136
00:09:38,035 --> 00:09:43,583
<b>[melancholic music continues]</b>

137
00:09:43,666 --> 00:09:45,126
<i><b>I'm happy with Ryan.</b></i>

138
00:09:46,961 --> 00:09:48,629
<i><b>With him and my daughter.</b></i>

139
00:09:49,880 --> 00:09:53,509
<i><b>I can see myself with them…</b></i>

140
00:09:53,593 --> 00:09:55,177
<i><b>forever.</b></i>

141
00:09:56,178 --> 00:09:58,598
<i><b>Then why are you leaving them?</b></i>

142
00:09:59,390 --> 00:10:01,517
<i><b>Because I'm sick of this.</b></i>

143
00:10:02,351 --> 00:10:04,812
<i><b>All my life, it's been like this.</b></i>

144
00:10:05,605 --> 00:10:08,149
<i><b>It's so damn tiring</b></i>

145
00:10:08,232 --> 00:10:13,195
<i><b>to be seen only as</b></i>
<i><b>the product of someone's affair.</b></i>

146
00:10:15,698 --> 00:10:17,408
<b>-[Beth sniffles]</b>
<b>-</b><i><b>See?</b></i>

147
00:10:17,491 --> 00:10:20,161
<i><b>Yes, you are</b></i>
<i><b>the result of the wrong choices</b></i>

148
00:10:20,244 --> 00:10:21,912
<i><b>made by adults, including me.</b></i>

149
00:10:21,996 --> 00:10:23,581
<i><b>So what?</b></i>

150
00:10:23,664 --> 00:10:25,249
<i><b>Now, you're an adult yourself.</b></i>

151
00:10:25,333 --> 00:10:28,794
<i><b>Don't you want to live</b></i>
<i><b>a life you chose for yourself?</b></i>

152
00:10:30,588 --> 00:10:33,215
<i><b>Don't be like</b></i>
<i><b>your father who thinks with his dick.</b></i>

153
00:10:34,008 --> 00:10:35,426
<i><b>He's got no balls!</b></i>

154
00:10:36,010 --> 00:10:37,928
<i><b>And don't be like me.</b></i>

155
00:10:38,846 --> 00:10:42,850
<i><b>Your flirt of a mother</b></i>
<i><b>said I look like a squid.</b></i>

156
00:10:44,518 --> 00:10:46,896
<b>[laughs]</b>

157
00:10:47,688 --> 00:10:50,024
<i><b>Don't let shame shackle you.</b></i>

158
00:10:50,107 --> 00:10:51,609
<i><b>That's what I did.</b></i>

159
00:10:52,818 --> 00:10:55,529
<i><b>Just because I was</b></i>
<i><b>scared of what others would say,</b></i>

160
00:10:55,613 --> 00:10:58,449
<i><b>I endured years of living a lie.</b></i>

161
00:11:00,409 --> 00:11:01,452
<i><b>Don't be like me.</b></i>

162
00:11:02,662 --> 00:11:05,456
<i><b>Do what would make you happy.</b></i>

163
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:11,796
<i><b>So there'd be one less</b></i>
<i><b>miserable person in this cursed town!</b></i>

164
00:11:16,008 --> 00:11:23,224
<b>[music turns hopeful]</b>

165
00:11:40,533 --> 00:11:47,456
<b>[hopeful music continues]</b>

166
00:11:49,125 --> 00:11:50,459
<b>Mm…</b>

167
00:11:52,878 --> 00:11:54,588
<i><b>Love? Ah--</b></i>

168
00:11:54,672 --> 00:11:56,090
<i><b>I fell asleep.</b></i>

169
00:11:56,173 --> 00:11:58,843
<i><b>It's okay. Want me to take Chloe?</b></i>

170
00:11:58,926 --> 00:12:00,553
<i><b>Yeah, she missed you.</b></i>

171
00:12:00,636 --> 00:12:02,471
<b>[Beth] You never found out.</b>

172
00:12:03,222 --> 00:12:04,598
<b>But…</b>

173
00:12:05,558 --> 00:12:07,601
<b>When I got back home, I realized,</b>

174
00:12:08,519 --> 00:12:10,229
<b>that this is what I wanted.</b>

175
00:12:10,312 --> 00:12:12,606
<b>I chose what I want in life.</b>

176
00:12:12,690 --> 00:12:14,024
<b>It's not perfect.</b>

177
00:12:14,942 --> 00:12:18,863
<b>And, yes, sometimes I still think</b>
<b>about the things I didn't get to do.</b>

178
00:12:22,992 --> 00:12:28,289
<b>It just hit me harder</b>
<b>when my friends returned.</b>

179
00:12:30,833 --> 00:12:35,754
<b>But if you strip away my</b>
<b>insecurities and dumb thoughts,</b>

180
00:12:37,173 --> 00:12:39,633
<b>this is the life I want.</b>

181
00:12:40,468 --> 00:12:42,052
<b>With you and Chloe.</b>

182
00:12:43,053 --> 00:12:44,305
<b>I want us.</b>

183
00:12:49,226 --> 00:12:51,604
<b>[Ryan sighs deeply]</b>

184
00:12:52,521 --> 00:12:54,106
<b>Love?</b>

185
00:12:55,357 --> 00:12:59,528
<b>Love, you can be angry at me,</b>
<b>but you can't not forgive me.</b>

186
00:13:00,988 --> 00:13:02,198
<b>Love?</b>

187
00:13:04,325 --> 00:13:05,743
<b>[sighs deeply]</b>

188
00:13:07,578 --> 00:13:10,206
<b>[sniffles] What matters is…</b>

189
00:13:12,625 --> 00:13:14,502
<b>you came back to us.</b>

190
00:13:18,088 --> 00:13:19,423
<b>-[sniffles]</b>
<b>-[Ryan chuckles softly]</b>

191
00:13:19,507 --> 00:13:21,842
<b>I know I don't deserve you,</b>

192
00:13:21,926 --> 00:13:24,512
<b>but I promise I'll make</b>
<b>up for what I did every day.</b>

193
00:13:24,595 --> 00:13:26,096
<b>-Hm?</b>
<b>-Mm-hmm.</b>

194
00:13:26,180 --> 00:13:27,348
<b>No more secrets, okay?</b>

195
00:13:27,431 --> 00:13:29,391
<b>-No more secrets. I promise.</b>
<b>-[Ryan chuckles]</b>

196
00:13:29,475 --> 00:13:33,020
<b>-[Ryan sighs in relief]</b>
<b>-[Beth whimpers]</b>

197
00:13:33,103 --> 00:13:38,526
<b>[hopeful music continues]</b>

198
00:13:40,778 --> 00:13:46,492
<b>[music swells]</b>

199
00:13:47,535 --> 00:13:49,578
<b>[Alice] There you go! Cute, no?</b>

200
00:13:50,412 --> 00:13:51,705
<b>-[Alice chuckles softly]</b>
<b>-[music fades]</b>

201
00:13:51,789 --> 00:13:55,167
<b>It's like the headbands</b>
<b>Auntie used to buy for me back then.</b>

202
00:13:59,505 --> 00:14:03,384
<b>[indistinct chatter from TV]</b>

203
00:14:03,467 --> 00:14:04,426
<b>Are you okay?</b>

204
00:14:09,098 --> 00:14:11,809
<b>I went to see Erica earlier.</b>

205
00:14:12,643 --> 00:14:14,436
<b>I had to give her something.</b>

206
00:14:17,106 --> 00:14:21,110
<b>Are you and Erica… better now?</b>

207
00:14:21,193 --> 00:14:22,778
<b>[sighs]</b>

208
00:14:23,654 --> 00:14:27,157
<b>I don't know if my visit helped</b>

209
00:14:27,241 --> 00:14:30,202
<b>or I just hurt her more.</b>

210
00:14:31,036 --> 00:14:35,249
<b>After she found out why Mama hated her…</b>

211
00:14:36,458 --> 00:14:40,212
<b>I don't know how we can ever be okay.</b>

212
00:14:42,172 --> 00:14:44,925
<b>She… She found out?</b>

213
00:14:45,634 --> 00:14:48,095
<b>[hesitates] Hasn't she told you?</b>

214
00:14:50,723 --> 00:14:52,474
<b>Sorry, uh…</b>

215
00:14:52,558 --> 00:14:57,730
<b>I thought you've heard</b>
<b>from Erica or Uncle Edward.</b>

216
00:14:58,606 --> 00:15:01,108
<b>I told Uncle Edward because,</b>

217
00:15:01,191 --> 00:15:03,402
<b>I needed someone to talk to about it.</b>

218
00:15:03,485 --> 00:15:07,364
<b>[woman crying on TV]</b>

219
00:15:07,448 --> 00:15:08,991
<b>What did she learn?</b>

220
00:15:11,952 --> 00:15:14,747
<b>I know this shouldn't come from me.</b>

221
00:15:16,373 --> 00:15:18,834
<b>But if I tell you…</b>

222
00:15:19,501 --> 00:15:24,381
<b>maybe you can help her be</b>
<b>more open to forgiving Mama.</b>

223
00:15:25,674 --> 00:15:32,640
<b>[unsettling music playing]</b>

224
00:15:46,820 --> 00:15:48,364
<b>[cop 1] Good evening, ma'am.</b>

225
00:15:48,989 --> 00:15:50,115
<b>[radio beeps]</b>

226
00:15:50,199 --> 00:15:52,159
<i><b>-Unit 12, requesting backup.</b></i>
<b>-Genero!</b>

227
00:15:52,242 --> 00:15:53,410
<i><b>There's a shootout in San Felipe.</b></i>

228
00:15:53,494 --> 00:15:54,828
<i><b>Officers down. I repeat,</b></i>

229
00:15:54,912 --> 00:15:56,538
<b>-</b><i><b>officers down.</b></i>
<b>-[radio beeps]</b>

230
00:15:57,164 --> 00:15:58,666
<b>[radio beeps]</b>

231
00:15:58,749 --> 00:16:00,584
<b>[cop 2] San Felipe? That's close by.</b>

232
00:16:00,668 --> 00:16:02,211
<b>[Genero] But</b>
<b>the next shift hasn't arrived yet.</b>

233
00:16:02,294 --> 00:16:04,505
<b>[cop 2] They're just five minutes away.</b>

234
00:16:04,588 --> 00:16:07,591
<b>Maybe we should leave now.</b>
<b>We're needed more in San Felipe.</b>

235
00:16:07,675 --> 00:16:09,468
<b>-[radio beeps]</b>
<b>-Dispatch Unit 9.</b>

236
00:16:09,551 --> 00:16:11,136
<b>We're on our way to the location.</b>

237
00:16:11,220 --> 00:16:13,013
<b>-[radio beeps]</b>
<b>-[car engine starts]</b>

238
00:16:13,931 --> 00:16:17,017
<b>[engine revs]</b>

239
00:16:17,101 --> 00:16:24,733
<b>-[police siren blaring]</b>
<b>-[unsettling music continues]</b>

240
00:16:24,817 --> 00:16:27,361
<b>[TV] </b><i><b>We don't want to</b></i>
<i><b>burden Auntie Maria any more.</b></i>

241
00:16:27,444 --> 00:16:30,239
<i><b>She's already letting us stay at her house</b></i>

242
00:16:30,322 --> 00:16:33,617
<i><b>and providing everything we need.</b></i>

243
00:16:33,701 --> 00:16:35,703
<b>-[Althea] Auntie?</b>
<i><b>-But she has kids, too.</b></i>

244
00:16:35,786 --> 00:16:37,997
<b>-Let's eat.</b>
<b>-[distant police siren blaring]</b>

245
00:16:38,080 --> 00:16:40,165
<i><b>You know I'm not earning enough.</b></i>

246
00:16:40,249 --> 00:16:43,293
<b>[woman on TV] </b><i><b>Pablo?</b></i>
<i><b>Come, love. Let's eat.</b></i>

247
00:16:43,377 --> 00:16:45,087
<i><b>Lunch is ready.</b></i>

248
00:16:45,170 --> 00:16:48,841
<i><b>-You, too. Come on. Follow me.</b></i>
<i><b>-</b></i><b>[siren continues blaring]</b>

249
00:16:52,428 --> 00:16:55,055
<b>[ominous music sting]</b>

250
00:16:55,139 --> 00:17:02,604
<b>[suspenseful music playing]</b>

251
00:17:02,688 --> 00:17:07,818
<b>[police siren blaring]</b>

252
00:17:18,287 --> 00:17:20,080
<b>[music fades]</b>

253
00:17:21,665 --> 00:17:22,833
<b>[Althea] </b><i><b>I know…</b></i>

254
00:17:24,043 --> 00:17:27,171
<i><b>that you can't just</b></i>
<i><b>forget everything Mama said.</b></i>

255
00:17:27,254 --> 00:17:29,089
<i><b>I know it hurts.</b></i>

256
00:17:29,173 --> 00:17:31,383
<i><b>And I'm not defending her.</b></i>

257
00:17:31,467 --> 00:17:33,343
<i><b>What she did was wrong.</b></i>

258
00:17:33,427 --> 00:17:36,972
<i><b>But me? I celebrate you.</b></i>

259
00:17:37,848 --> 00:17:40,225
<i><b>I miss you so much, Erica.</b></i>

260
00:17:43,062 --> 00:17:44,980
<i><b>I love you, Erica.</b></i>

261
00:17:47,107 --> 00:17:53,906
<b>-[panicked breathing]</b>
<b>-[foreboding music playing]</b>

262
00:17:53,989 --> 00:17:55,199
<b>Erica.</b>

263
00:17:56,950 --> 00:17:59,328
<b>Something happened.</b>

264
00:17:59,411 --> 00:18:06,210
<b>[ominous music playing]</b>

265
00:18:09,129 --> 00:18:10,130
<b>What happened?!</b>

266
00:18:10,881 --> 00:18:13,258
<b>When I got home, Cristina was all alone.</b>

267
00:18:13,342 --> 00:18:14,802
<b>Althea was gone.</b>

268
00:18:14,885 --> 00:18:16,970
<b>[Frank] I was supposed to pick her up,</b>

269
00:18:17,054 --> 00:18:20,599
<b>but she texted,</b>
<b>telling me to wait for her at the corner.</b>

270
00:18:20,682 --> 00:18:23,185
<b>But she didn't come.</b>

271
00:18:23,268 --> 00:18:24,561
<b>Didn't you see her leave?</b>

272
00:18:24,645 --> 00:18:27,523
<b>There was a miscommunication</b>
<b>during shift change.</b>

273
00:18:27,606 --> 00:18:31,193
<b>The cops before us left early,</b>
<b>thinking we'd be here in five minutes.</b>

274
00:18:31,276 --> 00:18:32,861
<b>But on the way,</b>
<b>we had to respond to a car accident</b>

275
00:18:32,945 --> 00:18:35,489
<b>and we weren't able</b>
<b>to tell our fellow cops.</b>

276
00:18:35,572 --> 00:18:38,450
<b>We thought</b>
<b>they wouldn't leave until we get here.</b>

277
00:18:38,534 --> 00:18:41,745
<b>For two hours,</b>
<b>there we no cops on duty here.</b>

278
00:18:41,829 --> 00:18:43,622
<b>We need to find her!</b>

279
00:18:43,705 --> 00:18:47,126
<b>I'm begging you! Please find my daughter!</b>

280
00:18:47,209 --> 00:18:48,669
<b>We'll call for backup.</b>

281
00:18:48,752 --> 00:18:52,381
<b>If you have a car,</b>
<b>please help us look for her.</b>

282
00:18:52,464 --> 00:18:54,007
<b>-That will be faster.</b>
<b>-Alright, sir.</b>

283
00:18:54,091 --> 00:18:55,425
<b>I'll just stay here.</b>

284
00:18:55,509 --> 00:18:58,804
<b>If Althea comes back,</b>
<b>I'll call you right away.</b>

285
00:18:58,887 --> 00:19:00,264
<b>-Go and find her.</b>
<b>-Yes, sir.</b>

286
00:19:01,598 --> 00:19:03,809
<b>[Annette sobs]</b>

287
00:19:03,892 --> 00:19:08,147
<b>[suspenseful music playing]</b>

288
00:19:08,230 --> 00:19:14,194
<b>[engines roaring]</b>

289
00:19:26,623 --> 00:19:31,336
<b>[engine continues roaring]</b>

290
00:19:31,420 --> 00:19:38,468
<b>[suspenseful music swells]</b>

291
00:19:50,189 --> 00:19:54,109
<b>[engines roaring]</b>

292
00:20:01,909 --> 00:20:07,122
<b>[suspenseful music continues]</b>

293
00:20:12,336 --> 00:20:17,049
<b>[engines revving]</b>

294
00:20:22,137 --> 00:20:28,101
<b>[suspenseful music intensifies]</b>

295
00:20:28,185 --> 00:20:31,355
<b>Help! Help! Help!</b>

296
00:20:31,438 --> 00:20:32,773
<b>Help!</b>

297
00:20:33,857 --> 00:20:35,776
<b>Help! Help!</b>

298
00:20:35,859 --> 00:20:38,028
<b>[man] </b><i><b>Help! Help!</b></i>

299
00:20:38,111 --> 00:20:42,866
<b>-[brakes squeal]</b>
<b>-Help! Help! Help!</b>

300
00:20:42,950 --> 00:20:46,453
<b>Th-There's a body</b>
<b>over there! I think they're dead!</b>

301
00:20:46,995 --> 00:20:48,705
<b>This way!</b>

302
00:20:49,873 --> 00:20:52,251
<b>-Where?!</b>
<b>-The body's over there!</b>

303
00:20:52,334 --> 00:20:54,002
<b>It's right there! II looks dead!</b>

304
00:20:54,086 --> 00:20:58,173
<b>[panting]</b>

305
00:21:00,175 --> 00:21:01,718
<b>[gasps]</b>

306
00:21:01,802 --> 00:21:05,514
<b>[dramatic music playing]</b>

307
00:21:05,597 --> 00:21:07,099
<b>Erica…</b>

308
00:21:15,232 --> 00:21:22,239
<b>[dramatic music continues]</b>

309
00:21:31,540 --> 00:21:34,376
<b>[crying] </b><i><b>Althea! Althea!</b></i>

310
00:21:34,459 --> 00:21:35,502
<b>[wheezing]</b>

311
00:21:35,585 --> 00:21:38,046
<i><b>I couldn't even save my own sister!</b></i>

312
00:21:38,130 --> 00:21:39,631
<b>[cries]</b>

313
00:21:39,715 --> 00:21:43,635
<i><b>It's such a lovely</b></i>
<i><b>sight to see you all fall apart.</b></i>

314
00:21:43,719 --> 00:21:45,887
<i><b>I'll help you with your mission, Edong.</b></i>

315
00:21:45,971 --> 00:21:47,723
<b>-[Edong laughs]</b>
<i><b>-I knew it.</b></i>

316
00:21:47,806 --> 00:21:49,516
<i><b>You want something from me, Attorney?</b></i>

317
00:21:49,599 --> 00:21:51,226
<i><b>Cooperate with us in catching Edong.</b></i>

318
00:21:51,310 --> 00:21:54,021
<i><b>You'll use me as</b></i>
<i><b>bait to catch that bastard?</b></i>

319
00:21:54,104 --> 00:21:56,398
<i><b>I knew you'd end up like me.</b></i>

320
00:21:56,481 --> 00:21:58,066
<i><b>No!</b></i>

321
00:21:58,150 --> 00:21:59,443
<b>-[flesh rips]</b>
<b>-[Edong yells]</b>
